0.body: This book is a Rust implementation of programs in Artifical Intelligence: A Modern Approach . For more complete examples please see the Java and Python repositories. Rust is a systems programming language that aims to be fast, reliable, and productive , and is already being used in major initiatives like HuggingFace's state of the art NLP tokenizers and Argo AI's autonomous driving platform . It has many features that make it an attractive choice for developing AI systems. One example is the basic safety guarantees provided: Programs that compile in standard Rust are guaranteed to be free of memory corruption. If you weren't aware, memory-corruption results in undefined program behaviour . Concurrent mutable access does not even compile . This in most cases eliminates concerns of "data races". Furthermore, higher-level abstractions in the language make it possible to develop similar ad-hoc safety guarantees for your own programs. If you are not already familiar with Rust, this may not be the best starting point. There is an excellent introductory book here that you can get started with and use alongside this repository. The documentation is gentle in the introductory sections but quickly builds up to assume that you have at minimum beginner knowledge of programming in Rust. Instructions on how to use this as a companion to studying the book goes here
